  "text": "Immortalized trophoblast cell line HTR-8/SVneo was established and maintained as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . After culture in RPMI 1640 (HyClone) with 2.5% FBS (HyClone) for 12 h, the cells were treated with a series of concentrations (0-200 ng/mL) of LPS in 10% FBS for 0-48 h. To investigate the relationship between NF-κB activation and cytokine secretion, the cells were cultured in the presence of LPS after treatment with pyrrolidine dithiocarbamate (PDTC, an inhibitor of NF-κB; Sigma-Aldrich) for 1 h. The cells were harvested for detection of NF-κB phosphorylated p65 (P-p65) and p65 protein, and supernatants were collected, centrifuged to remove cellular debris, and stored at -80°C for later analysis of cytokine secretion.",
